A first-grader was forced to sit on the floor of her Texas classroom with a clipboard for more than a month as punishment for drawing on her desk.

The Westwood Elementary student was sent to the principal's office, missed out on recess, washed the desk and wrote an apologetic letter to the janitor after  sketching in pencil in May.

But without informing the girl's parents, the teacher also punished the unidentified girl by making her sit on the floor.

