The girl went without a desk for more than a month, unable to see the teacher or blackboard, before she told her parents.

'I was never told that her desk was removed,' the girl's furious mother told KHOU 11.

'I asked her (the girl), 'Why did you not tell me?' And she said, 'I was too scared to tell you mama'. She thought what she had done was so bad she didn't deserve to have a desk.'

The mother is trying to transfer both her son and daughter to another school and has filed a grievance.

School district Spring Branch ISD told ABC 13 Eyewitness News the teacher was reprimanded.

'The family has been offered multiple opportunities to transfer their child, either to another teacher within the school or to any elementary school in the district where enrollment is not capped,' the district said in a statement.

